Supplementary Material. Appendix S3

Eric M. Wood, Ph.D - ericmwood@calstatela.edu - www.ericmwood.org

  • This is an R Markdown file associated with the paper Historical redlining practices are associated with present-day urban bird communities, their habitat, and the people who may experience them (Wood et al., Ornithological Monographs)

  • For all queries on the data analyses presented in this document, please contact the author.

Asian community

Asian ~ synanthropes - HOLC A

require(ggplot2)
require(MASS)
require(rsq)

m1   <- glm.nb(prc_u_fit ~ Asian_percent + I(Asian_percent^2),  data = subset_A)
summary(m1)

## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1

g1 <- ggplot(subset_A,
                aes(Asian_percent,
                    prc_u_fit)) +
  
  theme_bw() +
  
  theme(legend.position = "none") +
  
    
  geom_point(aes(colour = holc_grade),
             alpha = I(0.8),
             size = 2,
             position = position_jitter(height = 0.02, width = 0)) +
  
  geom_smooth(method="glm.nb",
              se=TRUE, 
              formula=y~x+I(x^2),
              alpha= I(0.3),
              size= 1,
              fill="slategray",
              fullrange = FALSE) +
  
  stat_smooth(geom="line",
              method="glm.nb",
              formula=y~x+I(x^2),
              se=TRUE, 
              alpha= I(0.5),
              size=1,
              color="gray12",
              fullrange = FALSE) +


  labs(x="Asian_percent", 
       y = "predicted synanthropic-bird abundance") +
  
  theme(text = element_text(size=12))
